"https://texaslawhelp.org/article/health-coverage-under-cobra-and-state-continuation\">https://texaslawhelp.org/article/health-coverage-under-cobra-and-state-continuation</a>  </li>\n<li>Texas Mini-COBRA | Health Insurance Coverage Continuation, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.cobrainsurance.com/usa-state-cobra-rules/texas/\">https://www.cobrainsurance.com/usa-state-cobra-rules/texas/</a>  </li>\n<li>LONG-TERM CARE INSURANCE REGULATION PROVISIONS - NAIC, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://content.naic.org/sites/default/files/model-law-chart-hs-15-long-term-care-insurance-regulation-provisions.pdf\">https://content.naic.org/sites/default/files/model-law-chart-hs-15-long-term-care-insurance-regulation-provisions.pdf</a>  </li>\n<li>28 Tex. Admin. Code § 3.3832 - Outline of Coverage | State Regulations | US Law, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3832\">https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3832</a>  </li>\n<li>Subchapter V. Coordination of Benefits 28 TAC §§3.3502, 3.3503, and 3.3510 INTRODUCTION. The Texas Department of Insurance (TD, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.tdi.texas.gov/rules/2024/documents/3502prop.pdf\">https://www.tdi.texas.gov/rules/2024/documents/3502prop.pdf</a>  </li>\n<li>TITLE 28 - Texas Department of Insurance, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.tdi.texas.gov/rules/2013/documents/final3_3501-3_35101.pdf\">https://www.tdi.texas.gov/rules/2013/documents/final3_3501-3_35101.pdf</a>  </li>\n<li>28 Tex. Admin. Code § 3.3077 - Minimum Standards for Specified ..., accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3077\">https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3077</a>  </li>\n<li>Individual and Group Health First Diagnosis or Critical Illness and Specified Disease Checklist - Texas Department of Insurance, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.tdi.texas.gov/forms/lhlifehealth/ah020.pdf\">https://www.tdi.texas.gov/forms/lhlifehealth/ah020.pdf</a>  </li>\n<li>Critical Illness - Texas Bar Private Insurance Exchange - Member Benefits, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://texasbar.memberbenefits.com/critical-illness/\">https://texasbar.memberbenefits.com/critical-illness/</a>  </li>\n<li>Payment may be used to help replace lost income or to help with expenses not covered by your medical plan or your disability inc - Webb County, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://webbcountytx.gov/RiskManagement/Supplemental/Supplemental-Forms/Cancer%20FAQ%20Flyer.pdf\">https://webbcountytx.gov/RiskManagement/Supplemental/Supplemental-Forms/Cancer%20FAQ%20Flyer.pdf</a>  </li>\n<li>Texas Insurance Code - INS § 1458.002 | FindLaw, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://codes.findlaw.com/tx/insurance-code/ins-sect-1458-002/\">https://codes.findlaw.com/tx/insurance-code/ins-sect-1458-002/</a>  </li>\n<li>28 Tex. Admin. Code § 3.3073 - Minimum Standards for Hospital Confinement Indemnity Coverage | State Regulations - Law.Cornell.Edu, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3073\">https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3073</a>  </li>\n<li>Texas short-term health insurance - eHealth, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.ehealthinsurance.com/texas-health-insurance/health-plans/short-term\">https://www.ehealthinsurance.com/texas-health-insurance/health-plans/short-term</a>  </li>\n<li>Finalized federal rule reduces total duration of short-term health plans to 4 months, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.healthinsurance.org/blog/finalized-federal-rule-reduces-total-duration-of-short-term-health-plans-to-4-months/\">https://www.healthinsurance.org/blog/finalized-federal-rule-reduces-total-duration-of-short-term-health-plans-to-4-months/</a>  </li>\n<li>Texas Insurance Code - INS § 1201.104 | FindLaw, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://codes.findlaw.com/tx/insurance-code/ins-sect-1201-104.html/\">https://codes.findlaw.com/tx/insurance-code/ins-sect-1201-104.html/</a>  </li>\n<li>28 Tex. Admin. Code § 3.3079 - Minimum Standards for Limited Benefit Coverage, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3079\">https://www.law.cornell.edu/regulations/texas/28-Tex-Admin-Code-SS-3-3079</a>  </li>\n<li>SUBCHAPTER Y. STANDARDS FOR LONG-TERM CARE INSURANCE COVERAGE UNDER INDIVIDUAL AND GROUP POLICIES, accessed March 27, 2026, <a href=\"https://www.tdi.texas.gov/rules/2001/ltc2.html\">https://www.tdi.texas.gov/rules/2001/ltc2.html</a></li>\n</ol>"
