      {
        "heading": "Top 25 facts to memorize",
        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<ol>\n<li><strong>Grace period minimums:</strong> 7 (weekly), 10 (monthly), 31 (other). citeturn30view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Notice of claim:</strong> by <strong>day 21</strong> or ASAP. citeturn20view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Claim forms:</strong> insurer must provide before <strong>day 16</strong> after notice or claimant can file written proof. citeturn30view2  </li>\n<li><strong>Proof of loss:</strong> due by <strong>day 91</strong>; late allowed if not reasonably possible, but generally ≤1 year (unless legal incapacity). citeturn32view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Time of payment:</strong> immediate on due proof for non-periodic losses. citeturn25view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Periodic payments:</strong> at least monthly; balance paid immediately at termination with proof. citeturn25view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Legal actions:</strong> not before day <strong>61</strong> after proof; not after <strong>3 years</strong> after proof was required. citeturn35view1  </li>\n<li><strong>Reinstatement:</strong> conditional receipt + no written disapproval → reinstatement on <strong>45th day</strong>. citeturn30view1  </li>\n<li><strong>Reinstatement coverage timing:</strong> accident after reinstatement; sickness begins <strong>&gt;10 days</strong> after reinstatement. citeturn30view1  </li>\n<li><strong>Incontestability (A&amp;H):</strong> after 2nd anniversary, non-fraud misstatements can’t void/deny certain claims beginning after that date. citeturn29view0  </li>\n<li><strong>A&amp;H preexisting after 2 years:</strong> claims beginning after 2nd anniversary can’t be denied for preexisting conditions unless excluded by name/specific description effective on date of loss. citeturn29view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Change of beneficiary:</strong> revocable beneficiary can be changed; beneficiary consent not required for surrender/assignment/change. citeturn34view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Payment of claims:</strong> death indemnity to beneficiary; other indemnities to insured; optional provider payment exists. citeturn33view0  </li>\n<li><strong>$1,000 cap</strong> on certain “equitable” payments to relatives when payee is estate/minor/incompetent. citeturn33view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Physical exam/autopsy:</strong> insurer’s right at its expense; autopsy only if not forbidden by law. citeturn35view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Misstatement of age (A&amp;H):</strong> benefit adjusts to what premium would have bought at correct age. citeturn26view1  </li>\n<li><strong>Change of occupation:</strong> more hazardous → benefit reduced; less hazardous → premium reduced + refund. citeturn26view2  </li>\n<li><strong>Illegal occupation:</strong> “contributing cause” felony/illegal occupation → insurer not liable. citeturn27view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Relation of earnings:</strong> DI benefits can be reduced proportionally + premium refund; <strong>$200 floor</strong>. citeturn26view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Right to examine (Texas A&amp;H):</strong> 10-day return/void + premium refund concept. citeturn8search3  </li>\n<li><strong>Medigap free look:</strong> 30-day free look concept. citeturn7search1  </li>\n<li><strong>Probationary waiting period:</strong> cannot apply to accident losses; sickness waiting period generally ≤30 days with stated exceptions. citeturn52view0  </li>\n<li><strong>Elimination period:</strong> initial period during a covered condition for which benefit won’t be paid; must be clearly shown/referenced. citeturn52view1  </li>\n<li><strong>Preauthorization:</strong> not a promise of coverage/payment. citeturn45search2  </li>\n<li><strong>Renewability disclosure:</strong> renewability provision must be appropriately captioned and on/referenced from first page; 10-point notices required for premium increase or age-based nonrenewal/termination. citeturn53view2turn37search0</li>\n</ol>"
      },
      {
        "heading": "Top 10 distinctions to avoid mixing up",
        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<ol>\n<li>Grace period (coverage continues) vs reinstatement (coverage restored after lapse). citeturn30view0turn30view1  </li>\n<li>Notice of claim (day 21) vs proof of loss (day 91). citeturn20view0turn32view0  </li>\n<li>Claim forms (day 16 fallback) vs proof of loss (substantive documentation). citeturn30view2turn32view0  </li>\n<li>Time of payment (when paid) vs payment of claims (to whom). citeturn25view0turn33view0  </li>\n<li>Probationary period (policy-start delay) vs elimination period (claim-start delay). citeturn52view0turn52view1  </li>\n<li>Preexisting condition definition/lookback vs probationary waiting period. citeturn52view2turn52view0  </li>\n<li>Exclusion (no coverage) vs limitation/reduction (less coverage). citeturn53view0  </li>\n<li>Noncancellable vs guaranteed renewable vs cancelable (what can insurer change). citeturn53view2turn38view0turn40view1  </li>\n<li>Misstatement of age/gender adjustment vs incontestability (different mechanisms). citeturn26view1turn29view0turn49view1  </li>\n<li>Change of occupation adjustment vs relation-of-earnings proportional reduction (risk class vs overinsurance). citeturn26view2turn26view0</li>\n</ol>"
      },
      {
        "heading": "Top 10 likely multiple-choice traps",
        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<ol>\n<li>90 vs <strong>91</strong> days for proof of loss. citeturn32view0  </li>\n<li>60 vs <strong>61</strong> days for lawsuit waiting. citeturn35view1  </li>\n<li>15 days vs “<strong>before the 16th day</strong>” for claim forms. citeturn30view2  </li>\n<li>Saying “incontestable means insurer can’t deny any claim.” citeturn29view0  </li>\n<li>Forgetting “fraud” exception in contestability concepts. citeturn29view0  </li>\n<li>Applying probationary waiting period to accidental injuries. citeturn52view0  </li>\n<li>Treating reinstated sickness coverage as immediate (it’s not; &gt;10 days). citeturn30view1  </li>\n<li>Confusing UCR with allowed amount or billed charges (and using billed charges for coinsurance). citeturn45search0turn45search1  </li>\n<li>Treating preauthorization as guarantee of payment. citeturn45search2  </li>\n<li>Confusing guaranteed renewability (policy continues) with premium stability (premium can change by class). citeturn53view2turn38view0</li>\n</ol>"
      },
      {
        "heading": "If you only had one hour to review this domain",
        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<p>Spend 45 minutes memorizing the “timing ladder” and the 2-year rules, then 15 minutes drilling classification differences.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Timing ladder to recite without hesitation: <strong>21 (notice)</strong> → <strong>16 (forms)</strong> → <strong>91 (proof)</strong> → <strong>immediate/monthly (pay)</strong> → <strong>61/3 years (sue limits)</strong>. citeturn20view0turn30view2turn32view0turn25view0turn35view1  </li>\n<li>The “2-year rules”: Incontestability and preexisting-condition limitation after the 2nd anniversary, with fraud carve-out logic. citeturn29view0  </li>\n<li>Reinstatement: <strong>45-day</strong> rule + <strong>accident now / sickness +10</strong>. citeturn30view1  </li>\n<li>Disability-income adjustments: change of occupation, illegal occupation (“contributing cause”), relation of earnings ($200 floor). citeturn26view2turn27view0turn26view0  </li>\n<li>Renewability: know what guaranteed renewable means, and know first-page notice requirements. citeturn38view0turn53view2turn37search0</li>\n</ul>"
      },
      {
        "heading": "Ready for architecture",
        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<p>Future course grouping recommendations for later (not building architecture yet):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>“Standard A&amp;H mandatory provisions” bundle (entire contract through legal actions) as one lesson cluster driven by timelines and rights. citeturn31view0turn29view0turn30view0turn30view1turn20view0turn30view2turn32view0turn25view0turn33view0turn35view0turn35view1  </li>\n<li>“Disability-income adjustment provisions” bundle (change of occupation, illegal occupation, relation of earnings, elimination period, recurrent disability if included later). citeturn26view2turn27view0turn26view0turn52view1turn44search1  </li>\n<li>“Cost-sharing &amp; limits vocabulary” bundle (deductible/copay/coinsurance, allowed amount, UCR, preauthorization, annual/lifetime limits). citeturn45search1turn45search0turn45search2turn45search3turn45search7turn45search9turn45search12  </li>\n<li>“Renewability &amp; cancellations/nonrenewal disclosures” bundle (TIC 1202.051, 1210.001, TAC 3.3038, TAC 3.3050). citeturn38view0turn37search0turn40view1turn53view2  </li>\n<li>“Riders &amp; policy options” bundle (impairment/exclusion rider logic, GI, waiver of premium, future increases, free look) with a tight focus on what changes coverage vs what changes premium obligations. citeturn53view0turn51search0turn51search2turn8search3turn7search1</li>\n</ul>"
      }
