        "heading": "Medicaid controlling/authoritative sources",
        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<ul>\n<li>Medicaid.gov program overview (state-administered, jointly funded) and eligibility policy pages (mandatory vs optional groups; general eligibility frameworks). These are <strong>directly testable</strong> at the concept level. citeturn15view2turn15view1  </li>\n<li>Medicaid.gov financial management / FMAP page. This is <strong>testable at the headline level</strong> (joint funding, FMAP). citeturn15view0  </li>\n<li>Medicare.gov Medicaid/dual-eligible explainer (Medicare first, Medicaid last; Medicaid covers some services Medicare does not). This is <strong>directly testable</strong> and exam-friendly wording. citeturn33view0turn29view1</li>\n</ul>"
