        "content_html": "<ul>\n<li>entity[\"organization\",\"Texas Department of Insurance\",\"Austin, TX, US\"] consumer workers’ comp insurance guide (subscriber vs non-subscriber, legal protection differences, and employer obligations). This is <strong>highly testable</strong> for Texas-specific framing and common wrong-answer traps. citeturn16view0  </li>\n<li>entity[\"organization\",\"Texas Department of Insurance Division of Workers’ Compensation\",\"Austin, TX, US\"] employee benefits overview (types of benefits, including income and medical benefits and death/burial). This is <strong>testable at a high level</strong> for “what benefits exist.” citeturn16view1  </li>\n<li>TDI coverage verification and non-subscriber reporting guidance (definitions of subscriber/non-subscriber and required notices/reporting windows). This is <strong>testable</strong> when questions ask about Texas employer obligations and whether coverage is mandatory. citeturn16view2turn16view3  </li>\n<li>Texas workers’ comp training deck (official TDI/DWC educational material): plain-language definition (“state-regulated, no fault, no blame”) and “not required for most private employers.” This is <strong>directly testable</strong> as a simplified authoritative statement. citeturn25view0turn25view1</li>\n</ul>"
