        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<ul>\n<li>entity[\"book\",\"Texas Insurance Code\",\"state insurance statutes\"] and entity[\"book\",\"Texas Administrative Code\",\"state insurance regulations\"] are cited in the exam’s own state-specific outline as controlling authorities (the exam points you there for state rule questions). In this Social Insurance memo, they chiefly serve as <strong>background support</strong> for private-product interaction (like Medigap rules), not for core Medicare/Medicaid federal program mechanics. citeturn23view0turn8search3  </li>\n<li>entity[\"book\",\"Texas Labor Code\",\"state labor statutes\"] is the legal base for many Texas workers’ comp rules; this memo relies on TDI/DWC authoritative summaries for test-prep emphasis. Background support for deeper legal precision. citeturn25view1turn16view1</li>\n</ul>"
