        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<ol>\n<li>The Commissioner is appointed by the Governor.  </li>\n<li>The Commissioner’s term is two years.  </li>\n<li>The Commissioner’s term ends Feb 1 of odd-numbered years.  </li>\n<li>Domestic carriers are examined at least once every 5 years.  </li>\n<li>New carriers (under 5 years) are examined in years 1, 3, and 5.  </li>\n<li>Maximum administrative penalty is $25,000 per violation.  </li>\n<li>A respondent has 20 days to answer a Notice of Allegations.  </li>\n<li>A Certificate of Authority is required for an insurer to transact business.  </li>\n<li>Transacting insurance includes soliciting, negotiating, and collecting premiums.  </li>\n<li>Domestic \\= TX; Foreign \\= Other U.S. State; Alien \\= Other Country.  </li>\n<li>Stock companies are owned by shareholders.  </li>\n<li>Mutual companies are owned by policyholders.  </li>\n<li>Fraternal societies use a lodge system and representative government.  </li>\n<li>Fraternals are exempt from state occupation taxes. 15. Temporary licenses are valid for 180 days and non-renewable.  </li>\n<li>A temporary license sponsor must be an agent, insurer, or HMO.  </li>\n<li>Temporary license holders cannot replace existing life policies.  </li>\n<li>Clerical employees are exempt from licensing if they don't receive commissions.  </li>\n<li>Insurers must notify the TDI of an appointment within 30 days.  </li>\n<li>Resident agents need 24 hours of CE every 2 years.  </li>\n<li>3 of those 24 CE hours must be Ethics.  </li>\n<li>50% of CE hours must be classroom or equivalent.  </li>\n<li>Longevity exemption (CE) requires 20 years of continuous TX licensure.  </li>\n<li>Failure to complete CE leads to a $50 per hour fine.  </li>\n<li>Address changes must be reported promptly to the TDI.  </li>\n<li>Twisting is using misrepresentation to induce a policy lapse.  </li>\n<li>Defamation is lying about another insurer’s financial health.  </li>\n<li>Claims must be acknowledged within 15 days of receipt.  </li>\n<li>Accepted claims must be paid within 5 business days.  </li>\n<li>Guaranty Association death benefit limit is $300,000 per life.</li>\n</ol>"
