        "heading": "**Top 15 Distinctions to Avoid Mixing Up**",
        "level": 3,
        "content_html": "<ol>\n<li><strong>Appointed vs. Elected</strong>: The Commissioner is appointed by the Governor.  </li>\n<li><strong>COA vs. License</strong>: COA is for companies; License is for individuals/agencies.  </li>\n<li><strong>Foreign vs. Alien</strong>: Foreign is U.S.-based; Alien is non-U.S. based.  </li>\n<li><strong>Suspension vs. Revocation</strong>: Suspension is max 1 year; Revocation is permanent.  </li>\n<li><strong>Rebating vs. Referrals</strong>: Rebating is illegal; Referrals are legal if not sales-based.  </li>\n<li><strong>Twisting vs. Churning</strong>: Twisting involves replacement via lies; Churning is internal replacement.  </li>\n<li><strong>Business Days vs. Calendar Days</strong>: Decisions take 15 business days; Acknowledgments take 15 calendar days.  </li>\n<li><strong>Individual vs. Aggregate Limit</strong>: Guaranty Assoc. has per-benefit caps AND a $300k overall cap.  </li>\n<li><strong>Domestic vs. Resident</strong>: Domestic applies to the company's origin; Resident applies to the agent's home.  </li>\n<li><strong>Agent vs. Agency</strong>: An agent is the person; an agency is the licensed legal entity.  </li>\n<li><strong>Notice vs. Decision</strong>: You have 15 days to acknowledge a claim, but 15 <em>business</em> days to decide.  </li>\n<li><strong>Classroom vs. Classroom Equivalent</strong>: Both count toward the 50% interactive rule.  </li>\n<li><strong>Fine vs. Penalty</strong>: CE deficiencies lead to $50 \"fines\"; code violations lead to $25k \"penalties\".  </li>\n<li><strong>Controlled vs. General Business</strong>: You must sell to the public, not just yourself.  </li>\n<li><strong>Member vs. Non-Member</strong>: Only member insurers are in the Guaranty Association (Fraternals are not).</li>\n</ol>"
