        "content_html": "<ol>\n<li>\"The Commissioner serves at the pleasure of the Governor for a four-year term.\" (False: 2 years).  </li>\n<li>\"A temporary license can be converted to a permanent license without an exam.\" (False: Exam required).  </li>\n<li>\"All 24 hours of CE can be completed via correspondence courses.\" (False: 50% classroom rule).  </li>\n<li>\"The Commissioner may fine an agent up to $100,000 for misrepresentation.\" (False: $25,000).  </li>\n<li>\"A foreign insurer is one incorporated in Mexico or Canada.\" (False: That is an Alien insurer).  </li>\n<li>\"The Guaranty Association protects policyholders of bankrupt Fraternal societies.\" (False: Usually excluded).  </li>\n<li>\"An agent can pay a $100 referral fee to a client for every policy the client’s friends buy.\" (False: Must be fixed, not sales-based).  </li>\n<li>\"A domestic insurer must be examined by the TDI every three years.\" (False: Every 5 years).  </li>\n<li>\"An agent has 60 days to report a felony conviction.\" (False: Promptly/30 days).  </li>\n<li>\"Claims must be paid within 30 days of the company receiving proof of loss.\" (False: 5 business days after acceptance).  </li>\n<li>\"Misrepresentation only applies to written advertisements.\" (False: Applies to oral statements too).  </li>\n<li>\"A stock insurer is owned by the people who buy the insurance.\" (False: That is a Mutual insurer).  </li>\n<li>\"Rebating is allowed if the client signs a waiver.\" (False: Always prohibited).  </li>\n<li>\"An agent can start selling for a company as soon as they mail the appointment form.\" (True: Provided it is mailed within 30 days).  </li>\n<li>\"The Commissioner can put an agent in jail for code violations.\" (False: Commissioner has administrative/civil power, not criminal).</li>\n</ol>"
